The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Nalco posts 28% rise in profit

 July 22 (PTI): National Aluminium Company (Nalco), the biggest smelter operator in India, today said its profit during the first three months of the current financial year rose 28 per cent to Rs 280.56 crore (or Rs 4.35 a share) from Rs 219.03 crore in the corresponding quarter last year. 

 The general increase in demand for aluminium in the domestic as well as in the international markets has spurred the profitability of the company. 

 HCC net up

 Hindustan Construction Company (HCC) has reported a 72 per cent increase in its first quarter net profit. 

 For the first quarter ended June 30, the company has posted its after-tax profit at Rs 22.66 crore against Rs 13.20 crore in the same period last year. The net sales for the reporting quarter rose 26 per cent to Rs 479.43 crore from Rs 380 crore. 




